{"key":"processedPost-6417766","value":{"id":6417766,"first":6403508,"last":6442832,"when":1167759779,"utime":"01/02/07 07:42 PM","content":"You can usually find a warm place without building one of those incubators.  Look at places such as above the kitchen cabinets, above and near the rear of the refrigerator near the condenser coils that radiate heat, the top of your water heater, etc.  Normal room temperature is fine, so just so you're in the mid 70F's to 80F, your jars will do fine.  Remember, every room is warmer near the ceiling than near the floor.  Get creative.<br />RR","title":"Re: INCUBATION OF INOCULATED JARS Temperature","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}